The paper deals with the design and analysis of sorting networks, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of SAT encoding suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the optimization of the networks using hand-crafted first layers and the improvement of upper bounds suggest a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
